reviewText: British movie that really could use subtitles... to make it understandable.
Sam Waterston is one of my favorite actors and I've been collecting his movies over the last several years.  Some are great, some are okay.  This one was okay.
funny story.  I wind up rooting for Sweet William wondering how long he can get away with it.

Horrible story, horrible acting, horrible direction, horrible production, horrible movie.
You can pick the movie at Goodwill tomorrrow.
Any Sam Waterston fan should watch this film of him from his sweet bird of youth. Very unlike Jack McCoy  This actor has tremendous range that was evident even back in his younger years.
